{
  "texts": [
    "Interest in evaluating and predicting student academic performance has increased with the developments of various predictive techniques in recent years.",
    "Many early studies have been conducted to analyze student's characteristics and evaluated their academic achievement and outcomes.",
    "Pantages and Creedon (1978) examined research conducted between 1950 and 1975 to identify the significant factors influencing student academic achievement.",
    "Moreover, Pascarella et al (1978) evaluated how interactions between students and faculty can help improve academic performance.",
    "Another study by Astin (1984) considered student's physical and psychological energy invested in the educational process and student involvement as important factors related to student learning and development, and therefore improve academic achievement."
  ]
}